  <p>
    When you buy a home on a septic system, you are buying something you can’t see — a private
    wastewater system that a standard home inspection usually doesn’t open or evaluate in depth.
    A dedicated septic inspection is how buyers turn that unknown into information before closing,
    which is exactly when it’s easiest to act on.
  </p>

